There are different serious challenges looming and in the proceeding hours of the event, in the form of climate change, sea-level, and rise in baseline- that are considered as factors in the exposure to Vietnam of the risk of natural disaster by their post-war level.

Vietnam’s vulnerability and its ability to reduce that vulnerability: The vulnerability that Vietnam has seen at the time of declaring themselves to be dependent on water is mostly based on manmade and natural reasons combined together. The main reason of this vulnerability was the war where the man-made destruction of the catchment areas especially the ones close to the Ho Chi Minh Trail has continued since the time 1954. On the other hand, the floods that are the aftermath of manmade destruction had been intensifying since the Vietnam’s independence. After this, the long years of war made the lake of Tonle Sap one of the most contaminated in the world and it resulted in the formation of ionized arsenic that is supposed to be the reason of the birth defects in the children born around that region. One also cannot forget the tribal people who have been trapped in puddle of them absence so for centuries. These people have been the ones who have been facing a new kind of vulnerability that is also man-made.
